## Sensitivity Prediction (mV/V)

Using a half-bridge Wheatstone configuration:

<div style="background:#f6f8fa; padding:12px; border-radius:6px;">
V<sub>out</sub> / V<sub>in</sub> ≈ (Gauge Factor × 2 × Strain) / 4  
<br>Gauge Factor ≈ 2.05, strain ε ≈ 1.055 × 10⁻³
</div>

**Predicted Sensitivity:** ≥ **1.0 mV/V** at 600 in·lbf  
This meets the project requirement and more than doubles the baseline sensitivity.

---

## Strain Gauge Selection

**Selected Gauge:** Vishay EA-06-125BZ-350  
**Type:** Linear foil gauge, 350 Ω, GF ≈ 2.05  

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr><th>Gauge Parameter</th><th>Value</th></tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr><td>Grid Length</td><td>3.18 mm</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Grid Width</td><td>1.57 mm</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Pattern Type</td><td>Linear</td></tr>
  </tbody>
</table>

The gauge geometry aligns with the mounting surfaces and FEM-predicted strain fields.

---

## Conclusion

The final torque-wrench configuration:

- Meets structural, fatigue, and fracture criteria  
- Achieves over twice the baseline sensitivity  
- Produces clean, predictable strain fields for half-bridge instrumentation  
- Demonstrates a complete design workflow: analytical → CAD → material selection → FEM  

This validated design provides a reliable, instrumented torque wrench suitable for experimental torque measurement.

